<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.61-62_0001a" />

<opener>
<dateline>
221 <hi rend="caps">W.</hi> Brandon Rd.<lb/>
Columbia, <hi rend="caps">MO.</hi> <lb/>
Dec. 11, '70<lb/>
Friday <hi rend="caps">P. M.</hi>
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I have just returned from the funeral of H. B. bless his truly noble soul! Rev. Crowley, of course, gave the talk, and it was a fine and well deserved tribute. He really got the spirit of the man

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.61-62_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>   <fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

I was so sorry you were unable to be present, and I hope you are not sick. Let me hear from you.</p>

<p>Hilda had a court case in Jefferson City and could not be with us; but Alice and I went together.</p>

<p>This carries love for you, dear Slade.</p>

<fw type="curatorial">61</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.61-62_0002a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

<p>We both know that H. B. is all right, that he is better off than we are. And to think how <hi rend="double underline">many</hi> care that he has gone <del/> on!</p>

<p>Yesterday, the <hi rend="underline">U</hi> of Mo. Library unveiled a fine painted portrait of me by the Hungarian artist, Franz <choice><sic>Szalsz</sic><corr>Szasz</corr></choice>. There was a nice ceremony &#8212; luncheon

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.61-62_0002b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>   <fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

and reception. The portrait is hung in the "Neihardt Room" with my Collection.</p>
<closer>
<signed>Kindest thoughts for Nita and love to you, Slade.</signed>

<signed>Gaki
(John Neihardt)</signed>
</closer>

<fw type="curatorial">62</fw>

</div1>
